The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Metro Recommends

 THE DVD

 (Landmark, Rs 995) This two-disc set features the 1992 

 concert in tribute to the charismatic Queen singer, who 

 died of AIDS. Artistes such as Metallica, Def Leppard, Elton 

 John, Axl Rose, Extreme and George Michael belt out some 

 of their own hits, perform Queen covers or jam with the 

 other members of Queen. 

 THE SHOW

 (Tollygunge Club, 6.45 pm, April 28, 29, 30) The multi-lingual 

 production steered by British stage director Tim Supple 

 features an all-Indian and Sri Lankan 22-member cast, including 

 three from Bengal. The piece using seven languages will 

 be presented by the British Council. 

 THE BOOK

 (Rs 

 425, Penguin) The authorised biography of Manjit Bawa has 

 been written by Ina Puri. It chronicles Bawa?s personal and 

 professional life, giving an insight into the experiences 

 and influences that have shaped him as an artist and a man. 




